laboratory_examinations.findings: Culture shows fewer than 1000 colony-forming units.

Specific gravity 1.018, pH 6.0; urine dipstick negative for leukocytes, nitrites, protein, blood, glucose, ketones, and urobilinogen. Sediment shows no bacteria, 0 to 1 white cells, no red cells, and no casts per high-power field.
Reveals bilateral grade III vesicoureteral reflux.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up radionuclide voiding cystourethrogram when the patient was 2.5 years of age still showed bilateral grade III vesicoureteral reflux.
Normal findings at presentation and follow-up.
